:: Start
Bologna. You are Caterina, 17 years old.
Your brother said girls are not welcome inside the Istituto delle Scienze.
So naturally—you came anyway.
The halls of Palazzo Poggi are silent. Glass cases line the walls: preserved animals, strange instruments, things better left unexplained.
Then you smell coffee. Fresh coffee. Somewhere nearby.
[[Follow the smell -> Corridor]]
[[Explore the museum first -> Museum]]

:: Museum
You stop at a display case.
Inside: a whale jawbone, a cracked globe, a rusted compass.
A brass plaque reads: Collected by Luigi Ferdinando Marsili.
The name feels familiar.
Then the smell of coffee drifts past again.
[[Follow it -> Corridor]]

:: Corridor
The corridor narrows.
At the end: a half-open door.
Warm light spills through the gap.
Inside, something clinks softly.
A cup?
[[Push the door open -> Study]]
[[Knock first -> Study]]

:: Study
The room is chaos.
Maps cover the walls. Glass jars cloud the shelves. Cannon sketches litter the desk.
Behind it sits an old man.
He looks up and smiles.
“Ah. Another curious intruder.”
[[Apologize -> Conversation]]
[[Stay silent -> Conversation]]
[[Ask who he is -> Conversation]]

:: Conversation
The old man gestures to a chair.
“Sit.”
You do.
He lifts a tiny porcelain cup.
“Coffee?”
You hesitate.
“I am Luigi Ferdinando Marsili.”
Your breath catches.
The founder. The explorer. The legend.
He points to the objects around him.
“Every one of these holds a story. Choose.”
[[The river maps -> X. The River, Drawn]]
[[The coffee cup -> VII. A Small Cup]]
[[The strange glass tube -> XI. The Ampoule]]
[[The cannon sketches -> VIII. The Dangerous Pages]]
[[Ask about his youth -> I. The Boy in Bologna]]
